rComments: Took the french class for health assessment. She has an amazing accent and speaks very well (no difficulty understanding what she is saying) especially important since I'm french immersion. didn't let us use translation dictionaries but would translate things using the internet so that was a good compromise. Happy, helpful and very specific.

Excellent prof. One of the best out there. She is straight forward with the content and tells you exactly whats important for exams. No surprises on the exams at all. Her slides are wonderfully organized. love her! she talks a bit fast. Makes an effort to finish the class earlier than the 3 hour mark which is awesome. If you get the chance pick her
